data.text:
31.10.2019., Zagreb, Croatia - After above average temperatures for most of October in the Croatian capital Zagreb, and an October record recorded on Sljeme, there has been a big drop with snow falling on Medvednica mountain this morning. According to data from the DHMZ weather station at Puntijarka, 4 cm of snow fell on Thursday on the Sljeme peak. With temperatures hovering around 0 Â°C and snow on the ground, there was a real winter look to Sljeme which was covered in warm sunshine just days ago. Photo: Igor Soban/PIXSELL

Captions are provided by our contributors.
